//@version=6
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  SKULD UNIFIED v2 — one indicator, self-switching by chart timeframe.
//
//  v2.1 (2026-07-21): APP toward-play — ride INTO a powerful level once
//     inside the approach window (1.0-1.5x target). With-move close, level
//     untouched in the lookback, one shot per level. Target lands at/just in
//     front of the level — never hold through it.
//  v2 (2026-07-21): DEVELOPING LEVELS ENGINE + VP visual overhaul.
//   · Live developing levels are first-class ranked levels now:
//       sPOC  (developing session POC)  rank 6 (session 1 + POC 5)
//       sVAH/sVAL (developing session VA) rank 4 (session 1 + VA 3)
//       dPOC  (developing DAY POC)        rank 8 (day 3 + POC 5)
//       dVAH/dVAL (developing day VA)     rank 6 (day 3 + VA 3)
//     Recomputed on every confirmed close from the fine-bin profiles,
//     drawn + ★-labeled, included in the MR pool and NEAREST panel.
//     The chart finally reacts to the CURRENT session, not just priors.
//   · VP style input: "Lines" (default — clean, draw your own profiles),
//     "Bars" (right-edge anchored, borderless thin rows), "Off".
//   · Defaults follow the 2026-07-21 shipped tuning: wick 0.55, cooldown 5,
//     tol 2×W, lunch/RTH-only/hard-cap gates OFF (all are toggles — flip for
//     strict plan mode). Dev-level signals test the LAST CONFIRMED level
//     snapshot; dev lines refresh on the first confirmed close after a
//     session roll (one live bar of lag at the boundary is by design).
//
//  ≥ switch TF (default 1H)  → STRUCTURE mode: weekly + daily ranked level
//     map, composite profile, clusters. No signals — this is the map.
//  < switch TF               → EXECUTION mode: session VWAP ±1σ/±2σ, ranked
//     level clusters, developing levels, and the plays:
//       IB  — THE set play: initial-balance acceptance break (9:30–10:30 ET)
//       MR  — everything else: reaction wick at a high-rank cluster
//       BRT — punched level retested from the other side and held
//       APP — approach: ride into a powerful level inside the window
//
//  LEVEL RANKING:  rank = scope + kind.
//     scope: session 1 · day 3 · week 5
//     kind:  POC 5 · VAH/VAL 3 · H/L 3 · HVN 2 · LVN 1
//     dynamic (fixed): VWAP 10 · day H/L 8 · dPOC 8 · ±2σ 6 · ONH/ONL 6 ·
//                      sPOC 6 · dVAH/dVAL 6 · IB 4 · sVAH/sVAL 4
//  CLUSTERING: levels within cluster width merge; rank = SUM; price =
//     rank-weighted mean. stars: ≥10 ★★★★★ · 8–9 ★★★★ · 6–7 ★★★ · 4–5 ★★ · ★
//
//  Candle-close confirmed only. No lookahead. No repaint.
//  One alert covers all: "Any alert() function call".
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
indicator("Skuld Unified v2 — Levels · IB · MR · BRT · Dev Levels", "SKULD", overlay = true, max_lines_count = 500, max_labels_count = 500, max_boxes_count = 500)

// ── ASSET AUTO-TUNE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
bool isES = syminfo.root == "ES" or syminfo.root == "MES"

